 ('52', '54', '4', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Flash Digest: News in Brief\",\"slug\":\"flash-digest-news-in-brief\",\"postDate\":1458766957,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"35\":\"By Gia Velasquez \\u2013 Edited by Olga Slobodyanyuk\",\"34\":[\"53\"],\"33\":\"<h3>The Federal Aviation Association Implements a Mandatory Registration Process for Drones<\\/h3><p><the federal=\\\"\\\" aviation=\\\"\\\" association=\\\"\\\" implements=\\\"\\\" a=\\\"\\\" mandatory=\\\"\\\" registration=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" drones=\\\"\\\">The&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.faa.gov\\/news\\/press_releases\\/news_story.cfm?newsId=19856\\\">mandatory registration process of small unmanned aircraft<\\/a>(UAS) by the Federal Aviation Association (FAA) in December drew<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.modelaircraft.org\\/gov\\/docs\\/AMAAnalysis-Closer-Look-at-FAA-Drone-Data_091415.pdf\\\">considerable speculation<\\/a>&nbsp;regarding the necessity of the registration process.&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/mercatus.org\\/publication\\/do-consumer-drones-endanger-national-airspace-evidence-wildlife-strike-data\\\">Researchers at George Mason University\\u2019s Mercatus Center<\\/a>&nbsp;investigated the risk of small drones on air traffic by studying the effects of wildlife collisions with aircraft and estimate that \\u201cone damaging incident will occur no more than every 1.87 million years of 2kg UAS flight time.\\u201d The study acknowledges that UAS may be more damaging to aircraft than wildlife, but conclude that the probability of a collision occurring is \\u201cat an acceptable level.\\u201d<\\/the><\\/p><h3><the federal=\\\"\\\" aviation=\\\"\\\" association=\\\"\\\" implements=\\\"\\\" a=\\\"\\\" mandatory=\\\"\\\" registration=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" drones=\\\"\\\">The FDA Expedites the Review Process for Generic Pharmaceutical Drugs<br><\\/the><\\/h3><p><the federal=\\\"\\\" aviation=\\\"\\\" association=\\\"\\\" implements=\\\"\\\" a=\\\"\\\" mandatory=\\\"\\\" registration=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" drones=\\\"\\\"><the fda=\\\"\\\" expedites=\\\"\\\" the=\\\"\\\" review=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" generic=\\\"\\\" pharmaceutical=\\\"\\\" drugs=\\\"\\\">The Food and Drug Administration has introduced an expedited&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.fda.gov\\/downloads\\/AboutFDA\\/CentersOffices\\/OfficeofMedicalProductsandTobacco\\/CDER\\/ManualofPoliciesProcedures\\/UCM407849.pdf?source=govdelivery&utm_medium=email&utm_source=govdelivery\\\">review process<\\/a>&nbsp;for generic pharmaceutical drugs that would compete with an off-patent drug produced by a single company. When a patent expires, the patent holder can raise drug prices because of its exclusive hold on the market, making it unattractive for new producers to join. Estimating the change will affect as many as&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bloomberg.com\\/news\\/articles\\/2016-03-14\\/shkreli-s-strategy-to-jack-up-drug-prices-may-be-curbed-by-fda\\\">125 generic drugs<\\/a>, the FDA hopes to foil plans of drug manufacturers such as&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bbc.com\\/news\\/world-us-canada-34331761\\\">Martin Shkreli<\\/a>, the former CEO of Turing Pharmaceuticals, who famously increased the price of an antiparasitic drug tablet from $13.50 to $750.<\\/the><\\/the><\\/p><h3><the federal=\\\"\\\" aviation=\\\"\\\" association=\\\"\\\" implements=\\\"\\\" a=\\\"\\\" mandatory=\\\"\\\" registration=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" drones=\\\"\\\"><the fda=\\\"\\\" expedites=\\\"\\\" the=\\\"\\\" review=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" generic=\\\"\\\" pharmaceutical=\\\"\\\" drugs=\\\"\\\">Senate Rejects GMO Labeling Bill<\\/the><\\/the><\\/h3><p><the federal=\\\"\\\" aviation=\\\"\\\" association=\\\"\\\" implements=\\\"\\\" a=\\\"\\\" mandatory=\\\"\\\" registration=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" drones=\\\"\\\"><the fda=\\\"\\\" expedites=\\\"\\\" the=\\\"\\\" review=\\\"\\\" process=\\\"\\\" for=\\\"\\\" generic=\\\"\\\" pharmaceutical=\\\"\\\" drugs=\\\"\\\"><strong><b><\\/b><\\/strong><\\/the><\\/the>The Senate rejected a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.npr.org\\/sections\\/thesalt\\/2016\\/03\\/16\\/470677241\\/bill-that-would-block-states-from-mandating-gmo-labels-stalls-in-senate\\\">bill<\\/a>&nbsp;that would have established voluntary labeling of genetically modified organisms (GMO). Democrat&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.nytimes.com\\/2016\\/03\\/16\\/business\\/senate-to-vote-on-gmo-food-labeling-bill.html?rref=collection%2Ftimestopic%2FGenetically%20Modified%20Food&action=click&contentCollection=timestopics&region=stream&module=stream_unit&version=latest&contentPlacement=1&pgtype=collection&_r=1\\\">Senator Jon Tester<\\/a>&nbsp;and organic farmer from Montana called the bill a \\u201cbad, bad, bad policy\\u201d because the voluntary standards \\u201care no standards at all.\\u201d If it had passed, the bill would have preempted&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.heritage.org\\/research\\/reports\\/2015\\/11\\/vermont-lawsuit-a-test-case-for-gmo-labeling-laws-and-the-first-amendment\\\">Vermont\\u2019s mandatory GMO labeling law<\\/a>, which is scheduled to take effect on July 1, 2016. Though GMO labeling is a highly disputed issue,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.forbes.com\\/sites\\/dalebuss\\/2014\\/02\\/20\\/americans-still-arent-buying-gmo-gospel-ask-general-mills\\/#c3153ae1d06a\\\">General Mills<\\/a>&nbsp;received no sales benefit from labeling Cheerios\\u00ae as GMO-free.<\\/p>\"}}', '2016-03-23 21:02:38', '2016-03-23 21:02:38', 'c944af49-42dc-42f4-8c3e-f9fe0e5bde2d');



